# Agent workflow (this repository)

Follow these requirements for implementation tasks, refactors, and non-trivial fixes.

## Plans and communication

- Use **checkbox task lists** in plans and status updates (markdown `- [ ]` / `- [x]`).
- Include a **clear definition of done** in every plan (concrete, verifiable outcomes).
- Provide a **summary of changes** when finishing or handing off work (what changed and why, at a high level).

## Code quality

- Add **comments on new or non-obvious code** (intent, invariants, or why—not narration of what the line does).
- Follow **existing project conventions** and common best practices for TypeScript, React, and this repo’s tooling (Biome, Vitest, Changesets as documented in `CLAUDE.md`).

## Tests

- **Adapt or extend unit tests** when behavior changes or new branches need coverage; keep tests meaningful (avoid trivial assertions).
